This paper deals with auction design, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves making allocation decisions in an online setting, which suggests a connection to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the impossibility of designing a truthful mechanism, which is a common concern in mechanism design and auction theory (cs.AI, cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves computing payments, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
